exist)\">2nd inauguration</a></li>\n</ul></td>\n</tr></table><p><b>Barack Hussein Obama II</b> (<span class=\"nowrap\"><small><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=American_English&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"American English (page does not exist)\">US</a></small> <span class=\"noexcerpt\"><a href=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/8/82/En-us-Barack-Hussein-Obama.ogg\" title=\"Listen\"><img alt=\

srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/3b/Speakerlink-new.svg/17px-Speakerlink-new.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/3b/Speakerlink-new.svg/22px-Speakerlink-new.svg.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"11\" data-file-height=\"11\"></a><sup><span class=\"IPA\" style=\"color:#00e;font:bold 80% sans-serif;padding:0 .1em\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:En-us-Barack-Hussein-Obama.ogg\" title=\"File:En-us-Barack-Hussein-Obama.ogg\">i</a></span></sup></span><span class=\"IPA nopopups\"><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Help:IPA_for_English&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Help:IPA for English (page does not exist)\">/<span style=\"border-bottom:1px dotted\"><span title=\"'b' in 'buy'\">b</span><span title=\"/ə/ 'a' in 'about'\">ə</span><span title=\"/ˈ/ primary stress follows\">ˈ</span><span title=\"'r' in 'rye'\">r</span><span title=\"/ɑː/ 'a' in 'father'\">ɑː</span><span title=\"'k' in 'kind'\">k</span></span> <span style=\"border-bottom:1px dotted\"><span title=\"'h' in 'hi'\">h</span><span title=\"/uː/ long 'oo' in 'food'\">uː</span><span title=\"/ˈ/ primary stress follows\">ˈ</span><span title=\"'s' in 'sigh'\">s</span><span title=\"/eɪ/ long 'a' in 'base'\">eɪ</span><span title=\"'n' in 'no'\">n</span></span> <span style=\"border-bottom:1px dotted\"><span title=\"/oʊ/ long 'o' in 'code'\">oʊ</span><span title=\"/ˈ/ primary stress follows\">ˈ</span><span title=\"'b' in 'buy'\">b</span><span title=\"/ɑː/ 'a' in 'father'\">ɑː</span><span title=\"'m' in 'my'\">m</span><span title=\"/ə/ 'a' in 'about'\">ə</span></span>/</a></span></span>;<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">[2]</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">[3]</a></sup> born August 5, 1961) is an <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Americans&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Americans (page does not exist)\">American</a> politician serving as the <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=List_of_Presidents_of_the_United_States&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"List of Presidents of the United States (page does not exist)\">44th</a> <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=President_of_the_United_States&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"President of the United States (page does not exist)\">President of the United States</a>, the <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=List_of_African-American_firsts&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"List of African-American firsts (page does not exist)\">first</a> <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=African_American&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"African American (page does not exist)\">African American</a> to hold the office. Born in <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Honolulu&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Honolulu (page does not exist)\">Honolulu, Hawaii</a>, Obama is a graduate of <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Columbia_University&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Columbia University (page does not exist)\">Columbia University</a> and <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Harvard_Law_School&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Harvard Law School (page does not exist)\">Harvard Law School</a>, where he served as president of the <i><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Harvard_Law_Review&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Harvard Law Review (page does not exist)\">Harvard Law Review</a></i>. He was a <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Community_organizing&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Community organizing (page does not exist)\">community organizer</a> in <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Chicago&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Chicago (page does not exist)\">Chicago</a> before earning his <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Juris_Doctor&amp;action=e
08-17 14:38:57.185 debug OkHttp dit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Juris Doctor (page does not exist)\">law degree</a>. He worked as a <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Civil_and_political_rights&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Civil and political rights (page does not exist)\">civil rights</a> attorney and taught <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Constitutional_law&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Constitutional law (page does not exist)\">constitutional law</a> at <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=University_of_Chicago_Law_School&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"University of Chicago Law School (page does not exist)\">University of Chicago Law School</a> between 1992 and 2004. He <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Illinois_Senate_career_of_Barack_Obama&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Illinois Senate career of Barack Obama (page does not exist)\">served three terms</a> representing the 13th District in the <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Illinois_Senate&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Illinois Senate (page does not exist)\">Illinois Senate</a> from 1997 to 2004, and <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Illinois%27s_1st_congressional_district_election,_2000&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Illinois's 1st congressional district election, 2000 (page does not exist)\">ran unsuccessfully</a> in the Democratic primary for the <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=United_States_House_of_Representatives&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"United States House of Representatives (page does not exist)\">United States House of Representatives</a> in 2000 against incumbent <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Bobby_Rush&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Bobby Rush (page does not exist)\">Bobby Rush</a>.</p>\n<p>In 2004, Obama received national attention during his <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=United_States_Senate_election_in_Illinois,_2004&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"United States Senate election in Illinois, 2004 (page does not exist)\">campaign to represent Illinois</a> in the <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=United_States_Senate&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"United States Senate (page does not exist)\">United States Senate</a> with his victory in the March <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Democratic_Party_(United_States)&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Democratic Party (United States) (page does not exist)\">Democratic Party</a> <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Primary_election&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Primary election (page does not exist)\">primary</a>, his <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=2004_Democratic_National_Convention_keynote_address&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"2004 Democratic National Convention keynote address (page does not exist)\">keynote address</a> at the <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=2004_Democratic_National_Convention&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"2004 Democratic National Convention (page does not exist)\">Democratic National Convention</a> in July, and his election to the Senate in November. He began his presidential campaign in 2007 and, after <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Barack_Obama_presidential_primary_campaign,_2008&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Barack Obama presidential primary campaign, 2008 (page does not exist)\">a close primary campaign</a> against <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Hillary_Clinton&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Hillary Clinton (page does not exist)\">Hillary Rodham Clinton</a> in 2008, he won sufficient delegates in the <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Democratic_Party_presidential_primaries,_2008&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Democratic Party presidential primaries, 2008 (page does not exist)\">Democratic Party primaries</a> to receive the presidential nomination. He then defeated <a href=\"/w/index.php?ti
08-17 14:38:57.185 debug OkHttp tle=Republican_Party_(United_States)&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Republican Party (United States) (page does not exist)\">Republican</a> nominee <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=John_McCain&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"John McCain (page does not exist)\">John McCain</a> in the <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=United_States_presidential_election,_2008&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"United States presidential election, 2008 (page does not exist)\">general election</a>, and was <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=First_inauguration_of_Barack_Obama&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"First inauguration of Barack Obama (page does not exist)\">inaugurated as president</a> on January 20, 2009. Nine months after his inauguration, Obama was named the <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=2009_Nobel_Peace_Prize&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"2009 Nobel Peace Prize (page does not exist)\">2009 Nobel Peace Prize</a> laureate.</p>\n<p>During his first two years in office, Obama signed into law <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Stimulus_(economics)&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Stimulus (economics) (page does not exist)\">economic stimulus</a> legislation in response to the <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Great_Recession&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Great Recession (page does not exist)\">Great Recession</a> in the form of the <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=American_Recovery_and_Reinvestment_Act_of_2009&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"American Recovery and Reinvestment Act of 2009 (page does not exist)\">American Recovery and Reinvestment Act of 2009</a> and the <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Tax_Relief,_Unemployment_Insurance_Reauthorization,_and_Job_Creation_Act_of_2010&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Tax Relief, Unemployment Insurance Reauthorization, and Job Creation Act of 2010 (page does not exist)\">Tax Relief, Unemployment Insurance Reauthorization, and Job Creation Act of 2010</a>. Other major domestic initiatives in his first term included the <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Patient_Protection_and_Affordable_Care_Act&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Patient Protection and Affordable Care Act (page does not exist)\">Patient Protection and Affordable Care Act</a>, often referred to as \"Obamacare\"; the <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Dodd%E2%80%93Frank_Wall_Street_Reform_and_Consumer_Protection_Act&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Dodd–Frank Wall Street Reform and Consumer Protection Act (page does not exist)\">Dodd–Frank Wall Street Reform and Consumer Protection Act</a>; and the <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Don%27t_Ask,_Don%27t_Tell_Repeal_Act_of_2010&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Don't Ask, Don't Tell Repeal Act of 2010 (page does not exist)\">Don't Ask, Don't Tell Repeal Act of 2010</a>. The legislation enforces limits on discretionary spending until 2021, establishes a procedure to increase the debt limit, creates a Congressional Joint Select Committee on Deficit Reduction to propose further deficit reduction with a stated goal of achieving at least $1.5\u00a0trillion in budgetary savings over 10 years, and establishes automatic procedures for reducing spending by as much as $1.2\u00a0trillion if legislation originating with the new joint select committee does not achieve such savings.<sup id=\"cite_ref-190\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-190\">[190]</a></sup> cooperation with Israel, including increased military aid, re-establishment of the <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Joint_Political_Military_Group&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Joint Political Military Group (page does not exist)\">U.S.-Israeli Joint Political Military Group</a> and the Defense Policy Advisory Group, and an increase in visits among high-level military officials of both countries.<sup id=\"cite_ref-294\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-294\">[294]</a></sup> The Obama administration asked Congress to allocate money toward funding the <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Iron_Dome&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Iron Dome (page does not exist)\">Iron Dome</a> program in response to the waves of <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Palestinian_rocket_attacks_on_Israel&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Palestinian rocket attacks on Israel (page does not exist)\">Palestinian rocket attacks on Israel</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-295\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-295\">[295]</a></sup></p>\n<p>In 2013, <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Jeffrey_Goldberg&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Jeffrey Goldberg (page does not exist)\">Jeffrey Goldberg</a> reported that, in Obama's view, \"with each new settlement announcement, Netanyahu is moving his country down a path toward near-total isolation.\"<sup id=\"cite_ref-Bloomberg_296-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Bloomberg-296\">[296]</a></sup></p>\n<p>In 2014, President Obama likened the <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Zionism&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Zionism (page does not exist)\">Zionist movement</a> to the <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=African-American_Civil_Rights_Movement_(1954%E2%80%9368)&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"African-American Civil Rights Movement (1954\u201368) (page does not exist)\">Civil Rights Movement in the United States</a>. He said that both movements seek to bring justice and equal rights to historically persecuted peoples. He explained, \"To me, being pro-Israel and pro-Jewish is part and parcel with the values that I've been fighting for since I was politically conscious and started getting involved in politics.\"<sup id=\"cite_ref-297\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-297\">[297]</a></sup></p>"},{"toclevel":3,"line":"Libya","anchor":"Libya","id":29,"text":"<div role=\"note\" class=\"hatnote\">Main article: <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=2011_military_intervention_in_Libya&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"2011 military intervention in Libya (page does not exist)\">2011 military intervention in Libya</a></div>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\">\n<div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\

In March, as forces loyal to Gaddafi advanced on rebels across Libya, calls for a no-fly zone came from around the world, including Europe, the <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Arab_League&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Arab League (page does not exist)\">Arab League</a>, and a resolution<sup id=\"cite_ref-298\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-298\">[298]</a></sup> passed unanimously by the U.S. Senate.<sup id=\"cite_ref-299\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-299\">[299]</a></sup> In response to the unanimous passage of <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=United_Nations_Security_Council_Resolution_1973&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"United Nations Security Council Resolution 1973 (page does not exist)\">United Nations Security Council Resolution 1973</a> on March 17, Gaddafi\u2014who had previously vowed to \"show no mercy\" to the rebels of Benghazi<sup id=\"cite_ref-300\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-300\">[300]</a></sup>\u2014announced an immediate cessation of military activities,<sup id=\"cite_ref-301\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-301\">[301]</a></sup> yet reports came in that his forces continued shelling Misrata. href=\"#cite_note-corruption_charges-404\">[404]</a></sup></p>\n<p>In December 2007, <i><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Money_(magazine)&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Money (magazine) (page does not exist)\">Money</a></i> estimated the Obama family's net worth at $1.3\u00a0million.<sup id=\"cite_ref-405\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-405\">[405]</a></sup> Their 2009 tax return showed a household income of $5.5\u00a0million\u2014up from about $4.2\u00a0million in 2007 and $1.6\u00a0million in 2005\u2014mostly from sales of his books.<sup id=\"cite_ref-406\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-406\">[406]</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-407\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-407\">[407]</a></sup> On his 2010 income of $1.7\u00a0million, he gave 14\u00a0percent to non-profit organizations, including $131,000 to <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Fisher_House_Foundation&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Fisher House Foundation (page does not exist)\">Fisher House Foundation</a>, a charity assisting wounded veterans' families, allowing them to reside near where the veteran is receiving medical treatments.<sup id=\"cite_ref-408\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-408\">[408]</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-409\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-409\">[409]</a></sup> As per his developed in his adult life.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Christian_413-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Christian-413\">[413]</a></sup> He wrote in <i>The Audacity of Hope</i> that he \"was not raised in a religious household\". He described his mother, raised by non-religious parents, as being detached from religion, yet \"in many ways the most spiritually awakened person that I have ever known.\" He described his father as a \"confirmed <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Atheist&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Atheist (page does not exist)\">atheist</a>\" by the time his parents met, and his stepfather as \"a man who saw religion as not particularly useful.\" Obama explained how, through working with <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Black_church&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Black church (page does not exist)\">black churches</a> as a <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Community_organizing&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Community organizing (page does not exist)\">community organizer</a> while in his twenties, he came to understand \"the power of the African-American religious tradition to spur social change.\"<sup id=\"cite_ref-social_change_414-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-social_change-414\">[414]</a></sup></p>\n<p>In January 2008, Obama told <i><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Christianity_Today&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Christianity Today (page does not exist)\">Christianity Today</a></i>: \"I am a Christian, and I am a devout Christian. I believe in the redemptive death and <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Resurrection_of_Jesus&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Resu
08-17 14:38:57.955 debug OkHttp rrection of Jesus (page does not exist)\">resurrection of Jesus Christ</a>. I believe that faith gives me a path to be cleansed of sin and have eternal life.\"<sup id=\"cite_ref-415\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-415\">[415]</a></sup> On September 27, 2010, Obama released a statement commenting on his religious views saying \"I'm a Christian by choice. My family didn't\u2014frankly, they weren't folks who went to church every week. And my mother was one of the most spiritual people I knew, but she didn't raise me in the church. So I came to my Christian faith later in life, and it was because the precepts of Jesus Christ spoke to me in terms of the kind of life that I would want to lead\u2014being my brothers' and sisters' keeper, treating others as they would treat me.\"<sup id=\"cite_ref-APbychoice_416-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-APbychoice-416\">[416]</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-ABCVideobychoice_417-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-ABCVideobychoice-417\">[417]</a></sup></p>\n<p>Obama met <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Trinity_United_Church_of_Christ&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Trinity United Church of Christ (page does not exist)\">Trinity United Church of Christ</a> pastor Rev. <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Jeremiah_Wright&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Jeremiah Wright (page does not exist)\">Jeremiah Wright</a> in October 1987, and became a member of Trinity in 1992.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Trinity_418-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Trinity-418\">[418]</a></sup> He resigned from Trinity in May 2008 during his first presidential campaign after <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Jeremiah_Wright_controversy&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Jeremiah Wright controversy (page does not exist)\">some of Wright's statements were criticized</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-419\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-419\">[419]</a></sup> The Obama family has attended several Protestant churches since moving to Washington, D.C. in 2009, including <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Shiloh_Baptist_Church_(Washington,_D.C.)&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Shiloh Baptist Church (Washington, D.C.) (page does not exist)\">Shiloh Baptist Church</a> and <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=St._John%27s_Episcopal_Church,_Lafayette_Square_(Washington,_D.C.)&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"St. John's Episcopal Church, Lafayette Square (Washington, D.C.) (page does not exist)\">St. John's Episcopal Church</a>.
